#!/bin/sh
# POSIX launcher: pick the committed binary matching this host's OS/arch and exec
# it. Lets the hook manifests call one stable path instead of mapping uname
# themselves. Windows hosts call bin/ponytail-windows-amd64.exe directly.
d=$(CDPATH= cd -- "$(dirname -- "$0")" && pwd)
os=$(uname -s | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')
arch=$(uname -m)
case "$arch" in
  x86_64 | amd64) arch=amd64 ;;
  aarch64 | arm64) arch=arm64 ;;
esac
exec "$d/ponytail-$os-$arch" "$@"
